    <title>Falling rods</title>

  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>
      Falling rods
    </h1>
    Two rods are dropped over a smooth table. In one case the end point on the 
    table can slide without friction, while in the other case it may rotate 
    around a horizontal smooth articulation. The simulation allows computing 
    fall times and trajectories.

    <ul>
      <li>
        You can select below the initial position of both rods by using the 
        slider or entering its initial slope as given by the angle <b>phi</b> 
        with the horizontal.
      </li>
      <li>
        Unit time is (<i>L</i>/<i>g</i>)<sup>1/2</sup>, where <i>L</i> is 
        rods' length.
      </li>
      <li>
        Put the mouse pointer over an element to get information about it.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </body>
